What is CSS?
- cascading stylesheets
- not a programming language
- stylesheet/ styling language
- used for website layout and design
- can be extended with Sass/Less

3 methods for adding CSS
- inline CSS
-> directly in the html element - no no
- internal CSS
-> using <style> tags within a single document
- external CSS
-> liking an external .css file
-> most recommended option 

CSS selectors
selector {
    property: value;
}

Colors in CSS
- color names
- HTML 5 color names
- Hexadecimal nums
- RGB (rbg{#, #, #})

Web safe fonts

Class and ID in CSS
- id: unique value
- class: reused 

Box Model
- Margin: spaces outside 
- Border:
- Padding: spaces inside
- Content:

e.g.
p{
    margin-top:5px;
    margin-bottom:5px;
    margin-right:10px;
    margin-left10px;
}

= to

p{
    margin: 5px 10px 5px 10ox;
    top->right->bottom->left
}

Positioning in CSS
- static
- relative
- absolute
- fixed
- initial
- inherit